Pre-Game Insights: The New York Mets host the Los Angeles Dodgers on Friday in Game 5 of the NLCS. The Dodgers lead the series 3-1 and can move on to the World Series with a victory.
PITCHING PROBABLES: Dodgers: Jack Flaherty (13-7, 3.17 ERA, 1.07 WHIP, 194 strikeouts); Mets: David Peterson (10-3, 2.90 ERA, 1.29 WHIP, 101 strikeouts)
BETMGM SPORTSBOOK LINE: Dodgers -132, Mets +112; over/under is 7 runs
Miscellaneous Highlights: The teams meet Friday for the 11th time this season. The Dodgers lead the season series 7-3.
Francisco Lindor leads the Mets with a .273 batting average, and has 39 doubles, a triple, 33 home runs, 56 walks and 91 RBI.
Shohei Ohtani leads Los Angeles with 54 home runs while slugging .646.
